<item>
            <title>[CODEC-72] Soundex and RefinedSoundex issues with character arrays</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-72</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Soundex and RefinedSoundex both have public US_ENGLISH_MAPPING char arrays. These don&apos;t appear to be used externally, so should be made private - or at least package protected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, the class constructors store externally mutable char arrays; it would be better if these were copied.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch to follow.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
